HEADWORD: Phlogistic
<hw>Phlo*gis"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Old
Chem.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to phlogiston, or to belief in its
existence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Inflammatory; belonging to
inflammations and fevers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phlogistical</ent>⟦br⟧
